# Finance Data Processing & Access Control Backend

## Project Overview

This project is a backend system built for managing financial records with role-based access control (RBAC). It simulates a real-world finance dashboard where different users interact with financial data based on their permissions.

The system focuses on clean architecture, structured API design, secure authentication, and efficient data handling.

---

## Tech Stack

* Backend: Node.js, Express.js
* Database: MongoDB (Mongoose)
* Authentication: JSON Web Tokens (JWT)
* Password Security: bcryptjs
* Environment Configuration: dotenv

---

## Key Features

### User and Role Management

* User registration and login
* Role-based access control (RBAC)
* Supported roles:

  * Viewer: Read-only access
  * Analyst: Read access with analytics
  * Admin: Full access (CRUD + user management)
* User status management (active/inactive)

---

### Financial Records Management

* Create, Read, Update, Delete (CRUD) operations
* Fields:

  * Amount
  * Type (income / expense)
  * Category
  * Date
  * Notes
* Filtering support:

  * By type
  * By category
  * By date range

---

### Dashboard APIs

* Total income
* Total expenses
* Net balance
* Aggregations using MongoDB pipelines

---

### Access Control

* Middleware-based role authorization
* Secure API endpoints
* Token-based authentication using JWT

---

### Validation and Error Handling

* Proper HTTP status codes
* Try-catch based error handling
* Meaningful error responses
* Protection against invalid operations

---

