## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/Manjeet300108/finance-backend
cd finance-backend

---

### 2. Install Dependencies

npm install

---

### 3. Environment Variables

The application uses environment variables for configuration. The following variables are required:

#### Local Development (.env)

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/financeDB
JWT_SECRET=secret123

---

#### Production (Deployment)

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster.mongodb.net/financeDB
JWT_SECRET=secret123

---

### Notes

* Replace `<username>` and `<password>` with your MongoDB Atlas credentials
* Do not commit the `.env` file to version control
* Use environment variables instead of hardcoding sensitive values

---

### 4. Run the Server

npm run dev

Server will run on:
http://localhost:5000

---

## Authentication Flow

1. Register a user → /auth/register
2. Login → /auth/login
3. Receive JWT token
4. Use token in headers:

Authorization: <JWT_TOKEN>

---

## API Endpoints

### Auth APIs

* POST /auth/register → Register user
* POST /auth/login → Login user

---

### Record APIs

* GET /records → Get all records
* POST /records → Create record (Admin only)
* PUT /records/:id → Update record (Admin only)
* DELETE /records/:id → Delete record (Admin only)

---

### Dashboard APIs

* GET /dashboard/summary → Get financial summary

---

## API Testing

All APIs were tested using Thunder Client (VS Code Extension).

This tool was used to:

* Send HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
* Test authentication using JWT tokens
* Validate API responses and error handling

---

## API Testing (Detailed)

### Register User

POST /auth/register

Request Body:

```json
{
  "name": "Manu",
  "email": "manu@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

---

### Login User

POST /auth/login

Request Body:

```json
{
  "email": "manu@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "token": "JWT_TOKEN"
}
```

---

### Authorization Header

Authorization: JWT_TOKEN

---

### Create Record

POST /records

Request Body:

```json
{
  "amount": 5000,
  "type": "income",
  "category": "salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "notes": "monthly salary"
}
```

---

### Get Records

GET /records

---

### Update Record

PUT /records/:id

---

### Delete Record

DELETE /records/:id

---

### Dashboard Summary

GET /dashboard/summary

Response:

```json
{
  "totalIncome": 5000,
  "totalExpense": 0,
  "netBalance": 5000
}
```

---

## Testing Workflow

1. User registered using /auth/register
2. Logged in via /auth/login to receive JWT token
3. Token added in headers for protected routes
4. Admin role assigned for testing record creation
5. All endpoints tested using Thunder Client

---

## Design Decisions

* MongoDB chosen for flexible schema and aggregation
* Modular architecture for scalability and maintainability
* Middleware-based RBAC for clean access control
* JWT authentication for stateless security

---

## Assumptions

* Default role is viewer
* Admin privileges required for data modification
* Authentication required for protected routes

---

## Future Improvements

* Pagination support
